doBeforeNodeDrop

boolean doBeforeNodeDrop(TreePanel treePanel,
                         TreeNode target,
                         java.lang.String point,
                         com.gwtext.client.dd.DragDrop source,
                         TreeNode dropNode,
                         DropNodeCallback dropNodeCallback)
Fires when a DD object is dropped on a node in this tree for preprocessing. Return false to cancel the drop.

Parameters:
treePanel - this
target - the node being targeted for the drop
point - the point of the drop - append, above or below
source - the drag source
dropNode - drop node provided by the source
dropNodeCallback - call setDropNode / setDropNodes on this callback to use a custon drop node. Can by used to drop a copy of the originally dropped node by cloning the dropped node and calling setDropNode on this callback
Returns:
false to cancel the drop
